        </statement>
        
        <solution>
            <p>
                To locate the centre of enlargement we follow the following steps:
            </p>

            <p>
                Draw lines connecting point <m>P</m> to <m>P'</m>,  <m>Q</m> to <m>Q'</m> and <m>R</m> to <m>R'</m> and extend those lines. The intersection point of those lines, will be the center of enlargement.
            </p>
            <figure xml:id="triangleprq1">
                <caption></caption>
            <image>
                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                <latex-image label="triangleprq1">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                         % Grid for reference
                        \draw[help lines, color=gray!30] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);

                        % Larger Triangle (Pink)
                        \fill[pink!70, opacity=0.6] (-3,-1) -- (2,3) -- (3,-2) -- cycle;
                        \draw[pink, thick] (-3,-1) -- (2,3) -- (3,-2) -- cycle;

                        % Label vertices of larger triangle
                        \node[left] at (-3,-1) {P'};
                        \node[above] at (2,3) {Q'};
                        \node[right] at (3,-2) {R'};

                        % Adjusted Smaller Triangle (Blue) - Moved slightly up and inside the larger triangle
                        \fill[blue!70, opacity=0.6] (-1.8,-2.5) -- (1,0) -- (2.3,-2.5) -- cycle;
                        \draw[blue, thick] (-1.8,-2.5) -- (1,0) -- (2.3,-2.5) -- cycle;

                        % Label vertices of the smaller triangle
                        \node[left] at (-1.8,-2.5) {P};
                        \node[above] at (1,0) {Q};
                        \node[right] at (2.3,-2.5) {R};

                        % Define the Centre of Enlargement
                        \coordinate (X) at (0,-4.2); 

                        % Continuous dashed lines passing through corresponding points until they meet
                        \draw[red, dashed, thick] (-3,-1) -- (-1.8,-2.5) -- (X); % A to P extended to X
                        \draw[red, dashed, thick] (2,3) -- (1,0) -- (X); % B to Q extended to X
                        \draw[red, dashed, thick] (3,-2) -- (2.3,-2.5) -- (X); % C to R extended to X

                        % Mark and label the Centre of Enlargement
                        \fill[black] (X) circle (2pt);
                        \node[below] at (X) {Centre of Enlargement};
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                
            </image>
         </figure>

        </solution>
